<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id748e325d-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s120108"><num value="120108">§ 120108.</num><heading> Records and inspection</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id748e325e-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s120108/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Records</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>The corporation shall keep—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id748e325f-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s120108/a/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> correct and complete records of account;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id748e3260-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s120108/a/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> minutes of the proceedings of the members, board of directors, and committees of the corporation having any of the authority of the board of directors of the corporation; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id748e3261-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s120108/a/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> at the principal office of the corporation, a record of the names and addresses of the members of the corporation entitled to vote on matters relating to the corporation.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="id748e3262-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7" identifier="/us/usc/t36/s120108/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Inspection</inline>.—</heading><content>A member entitled to vote on any matter relating to the corporation, or an agent or attorney of the member, may inspect the records of the corporation for any proper purpose, at any reasonable time.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id748e3263-3a70-11f1-9d9e-dfac6d46cab7">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/110/254/s1/a/2">Pub. L. 110–254, § 1(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="2008-06-30">June 30, 2008</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/122/2421">122 Stat. 2421</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
